        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 2:56PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 256 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of Mina, or 23 miles northwest of Coaldale, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mina, Junction U.S 95 And NV 360 (Tonopah Junction), and Mina
Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
